---
description: Require API documentation updates for every endpoint lifecycle change
alwaysApply: true
---

# API Documentation Discipline

- Any API endpoint created, modified, or removed must update **both** artifacts in the same task:
  - `docs/api/<module>.postman_collection.json` (Postman Collection v2.1 JSON, importable)
  - `postman/collections/DMS API/<module>/` (Postman native YAML workspace collection)
- Do not merge API changes with only one side updated.
- Contract fields must match across both artifacts: path, method, auth, headers, request body, success/error examples, and descriptions.
- For every `/api/v1/*` endpoint, document `X-Platform` and `X-Device-Id` as mandatory request headers.
- Saved API test cases and documented success/invalid-format examples must exactly match the response envelope actually returned by handlers.
- Keep `docs/modules/<module>.md` synchronized with endpoint flow details (middleware -> handler -> service -> business outcomes -> response mapping).

## JSON collection (`docs/api/<module>.postman_collection.json`)

- Must be valid Postman Collection v2.1 JSON (importable in Postman).
- Collection entries must include:
  - endpoint path
  - HTTP method
  - auth requirements
  - request payload
  - response payload
  - error responses
  - example request
  - example response

## Postman YAML collection (`postman/collections/DMS API/`)

Strictly follow the existing Postman native YAML layout and conventions.

**Collection root** (`postman/collections/DMS API/.resources/definition.yaml`):
- `$kind: collection`, description, optional `variables` (defaults only; prefer environment `base_url`).

**Module folder** (e.g. `auth/.resources/definition.yaml`):
- `$kind: collection`, `order` for folder ordering.

**Request file** (e.g. `auth/Login.request.yaml`):
- `$kind: http-request`
- `description`, `url: "{{base_url}}/api/v1/..."`, `method`, `headers`, optional `body` (`type: text`, YAML block scalar)
- `examples: ./.resources/<RequestName>.resources/examples` (relative path)
- `order` for request ordering within folder
- Auth: `Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}` when required
- Device context: `X-Platform: web`, `X-Device-Id: browser-1` on all `/api/v1/*` requests

**Example files** (e.g. `auth/.resources/Login.resources/examples/Success.example.yaml`):
- `$kind: http-example`
- Nested `request` (url, method, headers, body) and `response` (`statusCode`, `statusText`, `body.type: text`)
- File naming: `<Scenario Name>.example.yaml` (spaces allowed, matching existing convention)
- `order` for example ordering

**Folder layout for new endpoints:**
```
postman/collections/DMS API/<module>/
  <Request Name>.request.yaml
  .resources/
    definition.yaml
    <Request Name>.resources/
      examples/
        Success.example.yaml
        Invalid Request.example.yaml
        ...
```

## Postman environments (`postman/environments/`)

- Use `{{base_url}}` and `{{access_token}}` in requests; do not hardcode host URLs in collection files.
- Local: `postman/environments/local.environment.yaml` (`base_url: http://localhost:8080`)
- Staging: `postman/environments/staging.environment.yaml` (`base_url: https://stag-api.infiniour.com`)
